text.tspan: Does classification ability increase with age?
There is very strong evidence that the probability of making a correct
classification is higher for 6-7 year old children than for 4-5 year olds.
When new products are targeted towards children, different marketing strategies are
needed, depending on the age of the children. In one experiment, children of
different ages were asked to sort new drinks into categories 'milk' and 'juice'.
